{"cursor":"10624","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"{{infobox military conflict |conflict =Battle of MondovÃ¬ |partof =the French\nRevolutionary Wars |image = |caption =View of the Battle of Mondovi by Giuseppe\nPietro Bagetti (1764-1831) |date =21 April 1796 |place =MondovÃ¬, Piedmont, in\nmodern-day Italy |coordinates = |map_type = |map_relief = |latitude = |longitude\n= |map_size = |map_marksize = |map_caption = |map_label = |territory = |result\n=French victory |status = |combatant1 = French First Republic |combatant2 =\n|commander1 =Napoleon Bonaparte |commander2 =Michelangelo Colli-Marchi |units1 =\n|units2 = |strength1 =17,500 Rothenberg, p\n248 |strength2 =13,000 |casualties1\n=600 |casualties2 =1,600, 8 cannons |notes = |campaignbox = }} The 'Battle of\nMondovÃ¬' was fought on 21 April 1796 Chandler, Dictionary, p 283. Sources\ndiffer on the date. Smith and Rothenberg say 22 April. Fiebeger says 20\nApril. between the French army of Napoleon Bonaparte and the army of the\nKingdom of Sardinia-Piedmont led by Michelangelo Alessandro Colli-Marchi. The\nFrench victory meant that they had put the Ligurian Alps behind them, while the\nplains of Piedmont lay before them. A week later, King Victor Amadeus III sued\nfor peace, taking his kingdom out of the First Coalition. The defeat of their\nSardinian ally wrecked Austrian Habsburg strategy and led to the loss of\nnorthwest Italy to the First French Republic.\n","linknr":360,"url":"Battle_of_Mondovi","recorded":1375078420,"links":["/w/index.php?title=Battle_of_Mondov%C3%AC&action=edit","/w/index.php?title=Battle_of_Mondov%C3%AC&action=edit","//bits.wikimedia.org/favicon/wikipedia.ico","/w/opensearch_desc.php","//en.wikipedia.org/w/api.php?action=rsd","//creativecommons.org/licenses/by-sa/3.0/","/w/index.php?title=Special:RecentChanges&feed=atom","/wiki/Battle_of_Mondov%C3%AC","//bits.wikimedia.org/en.wikipedia.org/load.php?debug=false&lang=en&modules=ext.gadget.DRN-wizard%2CReferenceTooltips%2Ccha